2019 Week 6 Results

geru | 15 Oct 2019

Congratulations to this week’s winners:

  1. pshhidk - 169.94 fpts
  2. JekellP - 158.94 fpts
  3. rogdiaz - 156.74 fpts

After taking a week off from the top, pshhidk returns to become the first two-time 1st place winner and he accomplished this with zero unique draft picks. JekellP made a splash in his 2019 debut, coming in second. This week’s contest was the first time we had 19 members. While that created more competition, it also increases cash winnings. Keep submitting those lineups and let’s spread this money around.

After scoring just 1 TD in his first five weeks, Stefon Diggs (46.5 fpts $5,900) went crazy and scored 3 TDs on 7 REC for 167 YARDS. Another surprising player was Hunter Henry (33 fpts $3,600), this week’s Sleeper. He scored 2 TDs and got exactly 100 YARDS to earn the bonus and boost his total fpts to 33. Keep looking for those sleepers and value picks when you’re drafting.

This week’s Bye teams: Carolina, Cleveland, Pittsburgh, Tampa Bay.
